column2: #Small samples from a normal distribution, here is the result if we use Wilcoxon's signed rank test (Mann-Whitney test). But I think it makes more sense to use the t-test here since the residuals are normally distributed in these samples.
wilcox.test(flipper_length_mm ~ species, data = penguin_dat, alternative = c("two.sided"))
Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
